##A new case of pneumonia in a village called Oolong

Micro Signal biz-leaders

Function introduction, define Chinese commercial power

By Zhang Xia
Source: biz-leaders

By Zhang Xia

Source: biz-leaders

One

On the afternoon of February 17th, yesterday, my village suffered its worst panic since the outbreak.
Signs of panic were seen in the village commissary. About six o'clock in the evening, I accompany my mother to buy flour, the canteen owner told us that there is no 50 Jin of large bags of flour. "I don't know how, just a few people pushing a small cart, four or five bags to buy. " She muttered.
Questions were answered around 8:20 pm, and my friends, relatives and classmates began to circulate: Our County has the first new case of pneumonia confirmed! A photograph showing the circulation of the county people's Hospital, and a video of his village having been completely shut down has been widely circulated. The picture shows the patient, who was admitted at 16:05, diagnosed 40 minutes later and had contact with a new coronary pneumonia patient 27 days ago (January 21) .

Last night around 8:20, my county a new case of pneumonia confirmed news, began to spread among friends and relatives and Wechat Group

The village where the man who was diagnosed is located is only ten kilometers away from our village. There must have been some interaction between the villagers years ago. The wechat group, his contact tree diagram also shows that he had 27 days to the county seat, and the village many contacts, and before the second day of the Lunar New Year, to the outside village walk.
Even through the Internet, I can already feel the fear. In the group, many people remembered that he had been to the county supermarket where he had been. There are even concerns about the quality of care at county hospitals, assessing how many patients they can accommodate.
I will live the mother, is worried in advance once the whole county was closed, vegetables, meat and grain prices will rise. Regardless of the dark, my mother went to a grocery store and bought a carton of milk and a few jins of eggs.
And a pair of our village after the Lantern Festival, by the Henan mother-in-law returned to the mother-in-law, also became the object of anger.
"blame the outsiders. If it were not for the outsiders, how good our village, how safe? " My mother told me, in the commissary to buy people, is complaining. There's a virus out of town. It's part of their identity.

Two

In the memory of Song Hengrang, the village doctor, the last time the whole village was so frightened of outsiders, it was during the SARS period.
Song, 73, is now the oldest village doctor in the village. He only retired 13 years ago and has a 40-year medical history.
During the outbreak, Song, who has retired, assisted his son in the clinic to check the health of the villagers

At the time, he recalled, my village was also extremely nervous. At that time, there was a rumor spread in the village, "that disease, as long as the basic can not be cured. ". Every morning and evening, Song Hengrang and village leaders are carrying sprayers, spraying disinfectant in every corner of the village. The disinfection water is provided by the town government and needs to be checked regularly.
Three villagers, all returning from Beijing, were quickly quarantined. Song Heng let need to take their temperature three times a day, and then report statistics. Even so, the three villagers were the site of much trepidation in the village. Song Heng lets joke say, "even their home place Hutong at that time, a lot of people also walk around" . One of the quarantines, at one point complaining to him, "what am I, a rat? "
But as he has observed over the years, the damage to the village from a severe epidemic has not been great. After practicing medicine, he was most impressed by the epidemic prevention and treatment task is to vaccinate villagers against smallpox.
According to public records, smallpox was still one of the most deadly acute infectious diseases in the founding ceremony of the People's Republic of China. In 1952, the Ministry of Health issued a vaccination directive, ordering two hundred and sixty million vaccinations for that year. In 1966, the World Health Organization called for greater cooperation among countries to increase vaccination densities and eradicate the global smallpox epidemic.
Song Hengrang in 1967 accepted the unified training of the county hospital, began to practice medicine. The mission of smallpox vaccination in the countryside may have something to do with the World Health Organization initiative.
In his memory, he asked children and adults who did not have a history of vaccination to be vaccinated. Fortunately, our village has no history of smallpox, the majority of chickenpox infection. There are several people in the village in their 50s and 60s, who are known as "king hemp seed" and "Liu hemp seed" because of their scars from scratching chicken pox when they were young.
Another disease, the seven-day wind, which killed countless babies, was also eradicated around 1967. This was due to the unified training of rural midwives at that time. My 82-year-old grandmother, was recommended by the village, and Song Hengrang together in the county hospital training "classmate. ".
Grandma used to practice medicine as a midwife

According to Song Hengrang and Grandma, "seven days wind" should be tetanus, refers to the child after birth, convulsions, crying non-stop, fever and other symptoms, usually died within seven days. The main reason should be that most rural midwives do not have professional medical knowledge, cut the umbilical cord scissors is a household scissors, with white wine wipe, even if it is disinfected. Susceptible to infection and wind. After becoming a midwife in the village, the township health center provided grandma with gauze, bandages, medical alcohol, disinfectant and other materials on a regular basis. FORCEPS, forceps, tweezers and scissors were also provided by the hospital, the disease "seven days wind" disappeared in the village.

Three

In addition to smallpox and tetanus, Schistosomiasis and leprosy were eliminated as part of the mission.
The document, the Schistosomiasis directive, was issued in 1957, when song was 10 years old. He remembers taking blood samples from villagers around 1970, going from house to house every night with pieces of glass, sticking needles in the earlobes of sleeping children and adults, and giving them names, give it to the township health center.
The fear of leprosy is much greater. Perhaps is will cause the skin to be unusual and the limb end disability's reason, the patient is very taboo in the village. Our village has three cases, according to Song Hengrang and the village elderly, one of the disease was particularly serious, has been isolated in the hilltop hut, until his death did not marry. The village built him a stone house, dug wells, regular delivery of food, did not allow him to go down the mountain to fetch water. The misperception of the disease is evident in the presence of "leprosy" , and even in the threatening language of adults towards children.
Song's son, Song Lianning, is the second generation village doctor in the village and practices medicine with his father at the age of 19. According to his description, the most harmful to the villagers is actually the hygiene and health habits. Such as boils, lice, scabies, Eczema, Urticaria, etc. . When he was practicing medicine with his father in 1997, these skin diseases, which he did not pay much attention to changing the bedding or bathing, still occurred frequently.
According to his account, Lice and fleas once roamed the village. ASCARIASIS has long been a problem for rural children, too, mostly because of the habit of digging in the mud and sand, but not washing their hands. Then there is mumps, called "mumps" in the countryside. Often one child in the class gets mumps, and soon half of them fall ill. There is also "Pinkeye" , or trachoma.
One of the most serious diseases in the village was actually "hemorrhagic fever" . This is mainly due to the prevalence of rats and mice in the village. For a long time my village coexisted with all kinds of animals, such as owls, mice, weasels, bats and so on. It's not uncommon to see rats in a pancake stand or a wood-burning shed. Meat dishes or grain were bitten by rats, sometimes happen, people eat easily infected with hemorrhagic fever.
There are no fewer than ten patients with this disease in our village. There was an outbreak of the disease at the town high school.

Wanton

As for the current prevention and control of new crown pneumonia, as village doctors, Song Hengrang and Song lianning felt that the villagers were somewhat lax, and then too panic.

During the epidemic, the prevention and control of grass-roots hospitals is extremely strict, village health every day to record disinfection

Xu Is SARS period, the county has not been diagnosed with patients, the new pneumonia epidemic has just spread, most villagers are not vigilant enough. "How did this disease come to us? " Is Their usual language.
They say the disease, which spreads from big cities to the countryside, may not be spared. Kind of a fluke at the end of the battlefield.
In Song Hengrang and his son, this relaxation is another interpretation of what it is like to feel like a country with so much suffering and death.
Accidents happen all the time. Some people in our village once climbed up a walnut tree to break walnuts. They accidentally fell and hit the back of their head on a stone. Within half an hour, they also died. Because of the perennial planting of fruit trees, about ten times a year they had to hit pesticides, there have been many cases of lung cancer in recent years, some of them have gone to the hospital for chemotherapy, some of them are just waiting to die, some of them have killed themselves by drinking pesticides in order not to burden their families; some of the women suffering from breast cancer have delayed their treatment, eating toads and geckos raw at home.
The county is a big world to them, and an epidemic in an even more remote world is probably no more likely to happen to them than falling off a walnut tree.
But a panic that spreads because of a lack of information can also be powerful. The attitude towards the mother and son in the village who had returned from Henan was a case in point. After they returned to the village after the Lantern Festival, the whole village seemed to tense up. The village of pork and flour has also been snapped up a lot, because rumors will be completely "closed" the village.
Last night's flour rush was an example -- until this morning, when word finally came from the village that it was all a hoax. They said it was a misdiagnosis. The guy was just a contact for a confirmed patient, county's too nervous. Not After city tests.
As soon as the alarm went off, the villagers began to work up the hill again in the morning. Besides the epidemic, they're worried about the cherries in May.
But in the fields, the villagers put on a mask, as if because of the fear that came with the news, judging by their scattered, misinformed information, that the county could not cure the disease as long as it was there.
(the name of the person in the article is changed at the request of the interviewee)

In Song Hengrang and his son, this relaxation is another interpretation of what it is like to feel like a country with so much suffering and death.

Accidents happen all the time. Some people in our village once climbed up a walnut tree to break walnuts. They accidentally fell and hit the back of their head on a stone. Within half an hour, they also died. Because of the perennial planting of fruit trees, about ten times a year they had to hit pesticides, there have been many cases of lung cancer in recent years, some of them have gone to the hospital for chemotherapy, some of them are just waiting to die, some of them have killed themselves by drinking pesticides in order not to burden their families; some of the women suffering from breast cancer have delayed their treatment, eating toads and geckos raw at home.

The county is a big world to them, and an epidemic in an even more remote world is probably no more likely to happen to them than falling off a walnut tree.

But a panic that spreads because of a lack of information can also be powerful. The attitude towards the mother and son in the village who had returned from Henan was a case in point. After they returned to the village after the Lantern Festival, the whole village seemed to tense up. The village of pork and flour has also been snapped up a lot, because rumors will be completely "closed" the village.

Last night's flour rush was an example -- until this morning, when word finally came from the village that it was all a hoax. They said it was a misdiagnosis. The guy was just a contact for a confirmed patient, county's too nervous. Not After city tests.

As soon as the alarm went off, the villagers began to work up the hill again in the morning. Besides the epidemic, they're worried about the cherries in May.

But in the fields, the villagers put on a mask, as if because of the fear that came with the news, judging by their scattered, misinformed information, that the county could not cure the disease as long as it was there.
